Description: Egypt, medium group of standing adult males with two camels. Males wearing gowns and caps, European adult male at centre rear wearing military-uniform. Camels saddled with saddle-bags. Desert setting with trees. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Geography: Gîza possible location of "Pyramids". J M Hudson, 27/01/1997. Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
